description:
&quot;I am a tradesman not a polymath; why I know of planets and politics lies at their intersection with biological evolution.&quot;
— Stephen Jay Gould

&quot;In a crystal we have the clear evidence of the existence of a formative life-principle, and though we cannot understand the life of a crystal, it is none the less a living being.&quot; 
— Nikola Tesla

&quot;I can’t prove it, but I'm pretty sure that people gain a selective advantage from believing in things they can’t prove.&quot; 
— Randolph M. Nesse

&quot;Have not the small Particles of Bodies certain Powers, Virtues or Forces, by which they act at a distance, not only upon the Rays of Light for reflecting, refracting and reflecting them, but also upon one another for producing a great part of the Phænomena of Nature?&quot;
— Sir Isaac Newton
From Opticks, (1704).

&quot;The spectral density of black body radiation ... represents something absolute, and since the search for the absolutes has always appeared to me to be the highest form of research, I applied myself vigorously to its solution.&quot;
— Max Planck
